Checks if a number or word is less than or equal to another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
value1 <\= value2

Responses\:
success - The boolean operation was evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.
87940f3d-4360-4ca9-ace1-2dc4cf003de6.7cecfc92-f786-4b8f-b825-f8223c93e1b3.description=Starts the Parallel executions of the given flow in OO central based on the input list. 
Inputs\:
    workflowName 	- Name of the workflow to check.
    list - Comma Seprated list 
            Ex\: List of emails.
    numOfInstancesPerRun	- number of instances can run at same time.
    centralFlowPath 	- UUID or Complete Path of the flow in Central 
    flowInputName 	- Name of the input variable to pass the list values.


Results\:
    failedItems	- Number of list items failed
    successfullItems	- Number of list items successfull


Responses\:
    success 	- Opration executed successfully.
87940f3d-4360-4ca9-ace1-2dc4cf003de6.83ad6155-38b9-47d5-9ebc-ba2285046a03.description=Query Automation Database for all unprocessed reaudit/Scrub request. 87940f3d-4360-4ca9-ace1-2dc4cf003de6.aa1aab6b-4f92-4603-ac66-ed1aa9a7f56e.description=
This operation does not do anything. It can be used to filter flow variables by defining them as inputs and filtering them in the Results tab.

Inputs\:
    field1 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field2 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field3 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field4 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of  "field1" as it was specified at input or when filtered. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
